<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3373"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3373-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3373">Remove Impediments to Public Private Partnerships&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4870-4049">patricia.healy</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">5 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">To devise the best solutions to modernize government systems and processes, which will ultimately enable “Open Government,”  we need to bring people together from all sectors – federal, state, local and private – to brainstorm and collaborate on solutions to best update technology and other tools to modernize government systems that contain the data we need about government funding and program performance.  Further, given the status of the federal budget, funding for these kinds of efforts is unlikely to be widely available.<br/><br/>We need to explore mechanisms that allow free collaboration among the sectors without procurement barriers as well as alternative funding or sourcing options for solutions<br/></div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_3373" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_3373', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2248&topicID=3373')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_3373"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2248">Public-Private Partnerships</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_3373"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_3263">
